      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The thought of them being free without you is a heavy, but understandable, burden that many caregivers carry. It is not selfish to wish for their happiness, but letting go of your existence isn't a way to free them; it is a way to end your own life. Your presence, even when difficult, is the one thing they have to fight for, and that fight makes their love for you so powerful and precious.",
